# /commit â€” Format, Lint, and Commit Code Safely

This command automates best-practice Git commits by analyzing your working directory, staging changes, running lint checks, and committing.

## ğŸ§© What it Does

* Checks the current branch
* Runs type checks, formatters, and linters
* Generates a commit message
* Stages the appropriate files
* Builds production code (optional)
* Fixes basic errors where possible
* Commits changes atomically

